===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[Σοφοκλης]]

===Proper noun===
'''Sophocles'''

# A [[Greek]] [[dramatic]] poet (ca.495 BC – 406 BC); Sophocles was one of the three greatest Greek [[tragedian]]s. In the Athenian dramatic competitions of the Festival of Dionysus, he won more first prizes (around 20) than any other playwright, and placed second in all others he participated in. He is best remembered for his ''[[Oedipus]] Cycle'' of plays.

